The scoping document helped the team maintain realistic project boundaries during Sprint 2. Features categorised as “In Scope” focused mainly on usability improvements, support services, accessibility, navigation, and transport information.
More advanced features such as AI chatbot systems, real-time API integration, and advanced personalisation were classified as future improvements because they required more development time and technical complexity than the sprint allowed.
My contribution involved helping evaluate which features would provide the highest value to users while remaining achievable within the project deadline. 
This process improved my understanding of scope management, prioritisation, and agile decision-making.
